A Saudi Arabian man has been arrested at the Mexican border after attempting to flee the country to avoid facing rape charges in Utah .
Monsour Alshammari , 27 , is in the U.S. on a Saudi government student sponsorship and has ties to the country 's royal family .
He is set to be extradited back to Utah where he faces charges related to the rape of a student in February .
Utah police is being held at a facility in San Diego .